#!/bin/sh
# rply - Write a reply to selected text (email/WhatsApp) using LLM
# Usage in Sam: select text, then |rply
llm "Write a short, kind reply to the following message.
Output only the reply text, nothing else.
Don't add a subject line.
Keep it concise, factual, and natural.
Don't be effusive or gushy.
Don't commit to demands.
Use British spelling.
Match the formality level of the original message.
End the reply with an appropriate sign-off based on the tone:
- For most messages use: Kind regards, Bob Smith
- For warm or friendly messages use: Love Bob
- For formal or matter-of-fact messages use: Regards, Bob Smith

$(cat)"
